<h2 id=3D"idx_how_to_find_the_properties_of_a_rhombus">How to Find the Prop=
erties of a Rhombus</h2>
<p>
A rhombus is a type of <a href=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.com/parallelog=
ram-area-calculator/">parallelogram</a>, which is distinguished by all four=
 sides being of equal length. Its unique properties include its area, perim=
eter, angles, and the length of the diagonals.
</p>
<p>
You can calculate the value of these properties using one of several formul=
as.
</p>
<h3 id=3D"idx_how_to_find_the_area_of_a_rhombus">How to Find the Area of a =
Rhombus</h3>
<p>
You can find the <a href=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.com/area-calculator/=
">area</a> of a rhombus if you know the length of its sides and its height =
by using the following formula:
</p><div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_1_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad  adthrive-co=
ntent adthrive-content-1" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div>
