 0.6944em;"></span><span class=3D"mord mathnormal">h</span></span></span></=
span></span></div>
<p>
The area <em>A</em> of a rhombus is equal to the length of its sides <em>a<=
/em> times the height <em>h</em>.
</p>
<h3 id=3D"idx_how_to_find_the_perimeter_of_a_rhombus">How to Find the Perim=
eter of a Rhombus</h3>
<p>
Since a rhombus has four sides of equal length, you can find its <a href=3D=
"https://www.inchcalculator.com/perimeter-calculator/">perimeter</a> by mul=
tiplying the length of the sides by 4.
</p>
<div class=3D"latex latex--mh3 latex--left latex--mode-display latex--bg-gr=
ey loaded" data-latex=3D"" data-latex-alignment=3D"left" data-latex-mode=3D=
"display"><span class=3D"katex-display fleqn"><span class=3D"katex"><span c=
